The paper presents a game-theoretic approach to designing incentive mechanisms for risk management, which suggests that it belongs to the category of computer science and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also deals with security and IT risk management, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of algorithms and computer-assistance systems for risk management suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with large-scale risk management, which may fall under the category of complex systems (cs.CY).
